d 'BIASTEST': module to test parameter equality across different models
d
d  The biastest command in Stata is a powerful and user-friendly
d tool designed to compare the coefficients of different regression
d models, enabling researchers to assess the robustness and
d consistency of their empirical findings. This command is
d particularly valuable for evaluating alternative modeling
d approaches, such as ordinary least squares versus robust
d regression, robust regression versus median regression, quantile
d regression across different quantiles, and fixed effects versus
d random effects models in panel data analysis. By providing both
d variable-specific and joint tests, biastest command offers a
d comprehensive framework for detecting bias or significant
d differences in model estimates, ensuring that researchers can
d make informed decisions about model selection and interpretation. d
d KW: bias
d KW: parameter equality
d KW: regression
d
d Requires: Stata version 18
d
d Distribution-Date: 20250411
d
d Author: Hasraddin Guliyev,  Azərbaycan Dövlət İqtisad Universiteti
d Support: email hasradding@@unec.edu.az
d
